.TH "INQUIRE CURRENT ELEMENT TYPE AND SIZE" 3P "29 February 1991"
.SH NAME
INQUIRE CURRENT ELEMENT TYPE AND SIZE \- inquire the type and size of the current element
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SS C Syntax
.ft B
.ta 1.25i 2.75i
.nf
void
pinq_cur_elem_type_size ( error_ind, type, size )
Pint	*error_ind;	\fI\s-2OUT\s+2 error indicator\fP
Pelem_type	*type;	\fI\s-2OUT\s+2 element type\fP
size_t	*size;	\fI\s-2OUT\s+2 element size\fP
.fi
.ft R
.SS Required PHIGS Operating States
(PHOP, *, STOP, *)
.SH DESCRIPTION
.SS Purpose
\s-2INQUIRE CURRENT ELEMENT TYPE AND SIZE\s+2
returns the type and size of the current element.
.SS C Output Parameters
.IP \fIerror_ind\fP
A pointer to the location to store the error number of any error
detected by this function.
.IP \fItype\fP
Returns the type of the current element.
For example, a polyline primitive element would be returned as 
\s-2PELEM_POLYLINE\s+2, a character height attribute as 
\s-2PEL_CHARACTER_HEIGHT\s+2,
a modelling transformation as \s-2PEL_LOCAL_MODELLING_TRANSFORMATION3\s+2, 
and so forth.
The Pelem_type enumerated type is defined in phigs.h as follows:
