.fi
.IP \fIsize\fP
Returns the size, in bytes, that the application will have to allocate
in order to call \s-2INQUIRE CURRENT ELEMENT CONTENT\s+2
to retrieve the contents of the current element.
If the current element type is such that it is not necessary to allocate any
dynamic memory to retrieve its contents, a value of zero is returned.
.SH ERRORS
.IP 005
Ignoring function, function requires state (\s-2PHOP, *, STOP, *\s+2)
.SH SEE ALSO
.nf
.IP
.ta 0.5i
